@NODE Introduction "What is BlizKick anyway?"

     @{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}

BlizKick is used to rekick any @{"Kickstart ROM" LINK KickImage} with phase5/DCE turbo boards having @{"MAPROM" LINK MAPROMJumper} feature (jumper). Also many CPU Cards have this feature and are supported. Kickstart 1.2, 1.3, 2.04, 2.05, 3.0 and 3.1 are currently tested ROM images.

@{"SaveROM" LINK SaveROM} program can be used to save (grab) Kickstart ROM image into a kickfile.

@{"applypatch" LINK Usage3} program can be used to "prepatch" ROM image with BlizKick "patch" kind of @{"modules" LINK Modules}.

@{"romupdatesplit" LINK Usage4} can be used to split @{"AmigaOS 3.5/3.9 ROM Update file" LINK OS35setup}.

@{"loadresident" LINK Usage5} can be used to load resident tags to EXTRES buffer after running BlizKick. @{"protectextresbuf" LINK Usage8} can be used to MMU protect the EXTRES buffer area.

See @{"here" LINK Others}, if you want to know why you should use BlizKick instead of other similar programs.

See BlizKick package @{"features" LINK Features} and @{"requirements" LINK Requirements}.
@ENDNODE
